{
  "texts": [
    "Regarding literal translation examples, we can see in Figure 11, line ont-19 shows that clinical-WMT21fb gives more literal translation \"Mal función vesical\" than the preferred one \"Función vesical deficiente\" by clinical-NLLB when translating \"Poor bladder function\".",
    "The neural model output hallucinations can also be found in Figure 11, e.g.",
    "\"Vejícula\" does not exist and it is like a mix of \"vejiga\" and \"vesicula\" in Line ont_27;",
    "similarly, in Line ont_2, \"multicística\" is a mix of Spanish and English, because the correct Spanish shall be \"multiquística\".",
    "As we mentioned in Section 4., there are 4% Russian tokens in the English-to-Spanish translation outputs from the Clinical-WMT21fb model which can be observed in Figures 9 and 11."
  ]
}